description.narrative:
This five-year corefunding will contribute to Diakonia's themes of Human Rights and&nbsp;Socio-Economic Justice as it aims at a) fulfillment of Human Rights committments and b) fair distribution of wealth and acees to natural resources. ANND Goal: The role of a group CSOs in the Arab region is strengthened; their capacities are developed on social and economic policy-making processes ANND 2016-2020 Objectives are: O1. Increasing CSOs engagement in the Arab Watch report on Economic and Social Policies and enhancing its use in policy advocacy channels at national regional and international levels O2. Promoting coalitions and advocacy on social and economic rights using different channels (UPR and other treaty review mechanisms, LAS mechanisms). O3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Engaging ANND and its members in public debate around the implementation of the Agenda 2030 at the global, regional and national levels O4. Increasing CSOs engagement and developing their capacities on Trade and Investment policy making processes. O5. Increasing CSOs engagement and developing their capacities on taxation and expand the dialogue among CSOs, parliamentarians and labour groups as well as within public debates on the national level and regional levels. O6. Engaging ANND and its members in public debate around Business and human rights. O7. Improving monitoring, lobbying and advocacy with regards to the European Union (EU), International Financial Institutions (IFIs) and the League of Arab States. O8. Enhancing the outreach of the group of CSOs positions and database-ing at ANND.
